# DropFolio Core Guardrails

Use `DROPFOLIO_MASTERPLAN.md` as the source of truth for scope and architecture.

- Build one feature per prompt; avoid mixed-scope implementation.
- Keep all pages mobile responsive by default.
- Never change `middleware.js` auth behavior unless explicitly asked.
- Do not alter Mongoose models without explicit user confirmation.
- Keep `app/p/[slug]/page.jsx` as a server component.
- Route every Claude request through `lib/claude.js` only.
- Prefer conservative edits and preserve existing behavior.
- Do not introduce payments/Pro logic in MVP.
